 Business Briefs
																								 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The government has cleared 13 foreign direct investment proposals worth Rs 393.36 crore. Marutis proposed joint venture with Japans Futaba Industrial Co Ltd and Bloombergs plan to increase paid-up capital and enhance down-linking activities were among those to be approved. However, the proposal of Ford Automotive Finance Company India Pvt Ltd was rejected. Other proposals to be approved include the infusion of foreign equity of Rs 232.58 crore by Secunderabad-based Aster Infrastructure and Hyderabad-based kvk Energys plan to bring in 70 per cent foreign equity of Rs 97.06 crore to invest in downstream operating companies.																								 Calcutta, Oct. 4: JM Financial and an unidentified foreign private equity investor have bought a stake in Calcutta-based Shrachi groups realty business. A formal announcement on this is expected tomorrow. The Shrachi group, owned by the Todi family, is one of the leading developers in Calcutta. This is the fourth private equity investment in the citys realty market.																								 Calcutta, Oct. 4: Exide Industries Ltd will enter the lead smelting and recycling business to reduce the dependence on lead import. The board of directors also gave its approval to acquire a local smelter for Rs 25 crore. 																								 Mumbai, Oct. 4: The Reserve Bank of India today tightened the norms for sale of non-performing assets, directing financial institutions not to sell the bad debt below reasonable estimates.
